00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:25,310
You've already seen all the male guests.

594
00:22:25,310 --> 00:22:25,760
We...

595
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,310
Honestly,

596
00:22:26,310 --> 00:22:28,630
no interaction with them at all.

597
00:22:28,630 --> 00:22:29,470
We were competing.

598
00:22:29,470 --> 00:22:30,520
Yeah, from the start.

599
00:22:31,710 --> 00:22:33,710
But we've got muscular men.

600
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,110
Some are very tall.

601
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,560
Really?

602
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,710
Then how did you win?

603
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:38,470
We...

604
00:22:38,470 --> 00:22:39,110
Outsmarted them.

605
00:22:39,310 --> 00:22:39,920
Nah.

606
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,520
Seems like they have no intelligence.

607
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:42,590
You can't say it like that.

608
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:43,640
Just by luck.

609
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:44,710
We were luckier.

610
00:22:44,710 --> 00:22:45,190
So funny.

611
00:22:45,190 --> 00:22:46,430
Yes, pretty lucky.

612
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:47,710
Then we won.

613
00:23:26,710 --> 00:23:27,640
Quite a pity, right?

614
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:28,430
I missed out

615
00:23:28,430 --> 00:23:30,880
such a chance to enter Balance Island.

616
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:35,710
It ended so quickly.

617
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:36,590
I haven't even

618
00:23:36,590 --> 00:23:37,920
experienced the fun of this game.

619
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,230
I haven't even gone to fight yet.

620
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,000
It's quite a shame.

621
00:23:48,070 --> 00:23:48,710
I'm sorry.

622
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:49,310
It's okay.

623
00:23:49,310 --> 00:23:49,800
Sorry.

624
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:50,590
It's okay.

625
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:54,000
The competition is over.

626
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,590
Everyone, please get on the bus and leave.

627
00:24:19,710 --> 00:24:21,190
What are all your names?

628
00:24:21,190 --> 00:24:22,240
(Shy ice breaker)
Name.

629
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:22,920
What's your name?

630
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,070
My name is Yi Xiaofan.

631
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:25,310
Xiaofan.

632
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:26,470
Do you have a nickname?

633
00:24:26,710 --> 00:24:28,920
My nickname is Evan.

634
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:29,830
Evan.

635
00:24:29,830 --> 00:24:31,110
Okay, what about you?

636
00:24:31,110 --> 00:24:32,920
Usually everyone calls me Charlie.

637
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:34,070
Charlie.

638
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:34,630
That's catchy.

639
00:24:35,430 --> 00:24:37,430
Okay, I am Zhang Zizheng.

640
00:24:37,430 --> 00:24:38,520
You can call me Michael.

641
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,430
Michael.

642
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,950
Enda.

643
00:24:40,950 --> 00:24:42,640
Zhao Enda.

644
00:24:43,230 --> 00:24:44,040
My name is Ye Jiajie

645
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:44,500
or John.

646
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:45,110
Either is fine.

647
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:45,710
John.

648
00:24:45,710 --> 00:24:47,310
Okay, and Ye Jiajie is fine too.

649
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,800
(Shy, but speaks again)
I feel like you're all tall.

650
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:00,880
Seems I'm the shortest.

651
00:25:01,430 --> 00:25:02,590
But you're very strong.

652
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:03,900
I think I'll dream of you

653
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:05,300
(Shy with a bit of irony)
tonight.

654
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:08,920
(A familiar face in dream)

655
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,070
You are a warrior.

656
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:12,160
You all are warriors.

657
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:12,950
He is a predator.

658
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,040
I am his food.

659
00:25:15,310 --> 00:25:17,470
Feels like it's a survival game.

660
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:19,430
Not that serious.

661
00:25:19,430 --> 00:25:21,920
We're here to find our love.

662
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:23,110
Whether girls like you or not

663
00:25:23,110 --> 00:25:24,680
has nothing to do with the male rivalry,

664
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:25,470
honestly.

665
00:25:30,350 --> 00:25:31,470
Right from the beginning,

666
00:25:31,470 --> 00:25:32,430
they didn't do anything.

667
00:25:32,430 --> 00:25:33,470
They just observed.

668
00:25:33,470 --> 00:25:34,070
Exactly.

669
00:25:34,070 --> 00:25:35,680
Unlike you two who start off by fighting.

670
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:37,230
I mean, what can you achieve by that?

671
00:25:37,230 --> 00:25:38,230
You don't know anything.

672
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:40,160
I was already quite upset at the time.

673
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,430
A bit angry.

674
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,680
Xiaofan started with fighting.

675
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:45,350
This kind of behavior is not very good.

676
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,110
Combat requires strategy.

677
00:25:47,110 --> 00:25:48,310
Also, I think

678
00:25:48,310 --> 00:25:50,590
everyone should, while competing,

679
00:25:50,590 --> 00:25:51,880
still maintain some limits.

680
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:55,590
I think

681
00:25:55,590 --> 00:25:58,430
I misunderstood the competition,

682
00:25:58,430 --> 00:25:59,830
causing others to get hurt.

683
00:25:59,830 --> 00:26:01,280
I also got hurt.

684
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:03,680
So I felt a bit of guilt.

685
00:26:06,350 --> 00:26:07,880
I think it's okay.

686
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:08,700
Normally,

687
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:09,760
people treat it as a game.

688
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:11,680
To be able to fight with other guys

689
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:12,760
is a rare opportunity.

690
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:13,160
I think.

691
00:26:19,470 --> 00:26:20,470
Pristine.

692
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:23,230
I can't really imagine

693
00:26:23,230 --> 00:26:24,710
what the place we're going is.

694
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,710
I have no idea.

695
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:39,190
I probably wouldn't

696
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:41,070
visit a place like this on my own.

697
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:45,430
I think we might stay...

698
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:47,560
Are they going to have us
stay at the campsite?

699
00:26:48,310 --> 00:26:48,830
We lost

700
00:26:48,830 --> 00:26:49,350
after all.

701
00:26:49,350 --> 00:26:50,160
That's right.

702
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:50,920
Pitch the tent.

703
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:51,470
Yes.

704
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:57,640
We are losers.

705
00:26:58,350 --> 00:26:59,160
Losers, huh?

706
00:27:03,110 --> 00:27:04,470
Seems like we've arrived.

707
00:27:04,470 --> 00:27:05,280
That's the place.

708
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:06,760
Seriously?

709
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,560
Is that really a tent?

710
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:11,760
We're not going camping,

711
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:12,560
are we?

712
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:13,680
Maybe we'll stay here.

713
00:27:16,350 --> 00:27:17,310
No way.

714
00:27:17,430 --> 00:27:18,070
How come...

715
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:19,680
How come some are still broken?

716
00:27:20,230 --> 00:27:21,110
This is all drafty.

717
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:22,110
How can we sleep here?

718
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:25,110
This is a place for losers.

719
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:28,560
Losers walk.

720
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:31,710
Let's go.

721
00:27:35,710 --> 00:27:36,310
So windy.

722
00:27:56,830 --> 00:27:57,830
Amazing.

723
00:27:57,830 --> 00:27:59,400
Cook by ourselves?

724
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,760
I can't cook.

725
00:28:02,110 --> 00:28:03,640
Five islanders who failed to land,

726
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,350
you need to

727
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:05,920
prepare dinner for those

728
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,110
who are on the island.

729
00:28:08,830 --> 00:28:09,950
Congratulations, gentlemen,

730
00:28:09,950 --> 00:28:12,430
we have prepared an exclusive menu.

731
00:28:12,430 --> 00:28:14,350
You can decide tonight's dishes.

732
00:28:14,350 --> 00:28:15,470
I want this.

733
00:28:15,470 --> 00:28:16,710
Braised beef brisket with...

734
00:28:16,710 --> 00:28:17,470
Tomato and potato.

735
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:19,280
Dace with black bean and lettuce.

736
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,830
Is claypot porridge okay for you?

737
00:28:20,830 --> 00:28:22,070
Magically braised pork ribs.

738
00:28:22,070 --> 00:28:23,190
Korean style fried chicken.

739
00:28:23,190 --> 00:28:23,880
Vegetables.

740
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,000
Okay, what else?

741
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:25,800
Pick them all then.

742
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:26,640
See what they can do.

743
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:28,430
All in.

744
00:28:28,430 --> 00:28:29,800
Eggs in Korean soy sauce.

745
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:30,800
Pepper steak.

746
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:31,900
Egg butter bread.

747
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:32,950
Wide noodles with shrimp.

748
00:28:32,950 --> 00:28:34,190
Thai beef salad.

749
00:28:34,190 --> 00:28:36,000
Fried Shrimp and burdock roll.

750
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:37,190
Sesame salmon.

751
00:28:37,190 --> 00:28:38,190
Onion sushi.

752
00:28:38,190 --> 00:28:39,380
Scrambled eggs with tomatoes.

753
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,470
Because everyone wants

754
00:28:41,470 --> 00:28:42,560
different dishes.

755
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,520
Since that's the case,

756
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:44,350
order them all

757
00:28:44,350 --> 00:28:45,520
and eat them all.

758
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:46,880
Fifteen dishes.

759
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:47,640
So many.

760
00:28:49,350 --> 00:28:51,310
Feels like this might be the last activity

761
00:28:51,310 --> 00:28:53,000
of the day. Keep cooking.

762
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:54,520
Yeah.

763
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,070
Cooking? It was quite surprising.

764
00:28:57,070 --> 00:28:58,160
It's a lot of pressure too.

765
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,470
Because I rarely cook.

766
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:00,680
I've never even cooked before.

767
00:29:00,950 --> 00:29:02,310
When was the last time you cooked?

768
00:29:02,560 --> 00:29:03,160
The last time?

769
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:04,070
Yeah.

770
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:07,040
Apart from cooking noodles,

771
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:08,000
it should be...

772
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:08,590
Noodles...

773
00:29:08,590 --> 00:29:09,430
Instant noodles?

774
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:11,040
Me too.

775
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:12,950
Seems like it's our first time.

776
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:16,350
I don't usually have the time to cook.

777
00:29:20,230 --> 00:29:22,350
You can tell at a glance, he's a chef.

778
00:29:29,430 --> 00:29:30,520
Only one type of shrimp?

779
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,110
Yes.

780
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:32,160
Can you save a few for me?

781
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:33,350
I want eight.

782
00:29:33,710 --> 00:29:34,920
Eight, so precise.

783
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:35,230
Eight.

784
00:29:35,230 --> 00:29:36,230
Sure, no problem.

785
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,310
Save five cherry tomatoes for me.

786
00:29:39,310 --> 00:29:40,280
Okay.

787
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:41,760
Seems like there isn't a scale.

788
00:29:42,430 --> 00:29:43,760
Did you wash the vegetables?

789
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:45,830
No.

790
00:29:45,830 --> 00:29:46,310
Oh.

791
00:29:46,310 --> 00:29:46,920
No.

792
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:47,520
We didn't.

793
00:29:51,110 --> 00:29:52,070
It's covered in dirt.

794
00:29:52,070 --> 00:29:52,950
Luckily I washed it.

795
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,950
I don't know whether they washed

796
00:29:54,950 --> 00:29:55,760
other vegetables.

797
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:58,190
It seems

798
00:29:58,190 --> 00:29:59,110
one of them didn't.

799
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:00,010
But he still cooked it.

800
00:30:00,110 --> 00:30:01,430
Which dish did he make?

801
00:30:01,430 --> 00:30:02,520
I think I won't eat it.

802
00:30:17,830 --> 00:30:19,160
That's very professional.

803
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:20,520
Like Omakase.

804
00:30:20,710 --> 00:30:22,040
This is something I can't learn.

805
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:23,560
Feels just like a chef.

806
00:30:24,830 --> 00:30:25,760
I can cook.

807
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:27,000
I studies culinary arts

808
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,230
in high school and university.

809
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:31,640
Here comes the food.

810
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,430
Legs.

811
00:30:33,430 --> 00:30:34,070
Look.

812
00:30:34,070 --> 00:30:35,190
All the legs.

813
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:40,190
Maybe for other people,

814
00:30:40,190 --> 00:30:42,470
this cooking part is a punishment.

815
00:30:42,470 --> 00:30:45,230
But I really enjoy
the process of cooking.

816
00:30:53,830 --> 00:30:54,760
Boss,

817
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:56,350
which one do you want to eat today?

818
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:57,160
This one?

819
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:57,880
Or this one?

820
00:30:58,070 --> 00:30:58,880
Which one?

821
00:30:59,950 --> 00:31:01,560
Boss, is it okay if we go with this?

822
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:03,280
If no female guest chooses me,

823
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,230
can I have a dinner swith you?

824
00:31:06,470 --> 00:31:07,350
Is that okay?

825
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,680
So, guys who can cook

826
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,470
earn extra points in your hearts?

827
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:13,310
Exactly.

828
00:31:13,310 --> 00:31:13,710
Yes.

829
00:31:13,710 --> 00:31:14,640
Definitely.

830
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,400
Being able to cook is a plus?

831
00:31:16,590 --> 00:31:17,470
Yeah, it is.

832
00:31:17,470 --> 00:31:19,430
That's bad.

833
00:31:20,590 --> 00:31:21,420
That's bad.

834
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:24,640
I didn't expect cooking
to be so difficult.

835
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:25,880
Where is this dish from?

836
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:27,430
Shanghai.

837
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:29,680
Shanghai cuisine.

838
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:31,760
Incredible.

839
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:32,680
Benbang cuisine.

840
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:33,880
Benbang cuisine.

841
00:31:34,190 --> 00:31:35,070
Sir from Beijing,

842
00:31:35,070 --> 00:31:37,560
you seem to be visiting Shanghai
more often.

843
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:38,400
Exactly.

844
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:39,680
Alright.

845
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:41,590
Now I understand

846
00:31:41,590 --> 00:31:43,160
the importance of those two keys.

847
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:44,640
Exactly.

848
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:48,190
It's all because Evan bumped into me.

849
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:50,400
I'm curious about what they're doing.

850
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:52,190
We are working hard cooking.

851
00:31:52,460 --> 00:31:53,660
(They are...)

852
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,070
Which way?

853
00:31:54,070 --> 00:31:54,470
Go on.

854
00:31:54,470 --> 00:31:55,280
This way.

855
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:55,880
Here?

856
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:56,560
Yes.

857
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:58,040
Are we really going downhill?

858
00:31:58,590 --> 00:32:01,190
Be careful with this.

859
00:32:01,190 --> 00:32:01,950
Can you?

860
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,470
You can take my arm.

861
00:32:04,470 --> 00:32:05,280
Thank you.

862
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,590
I feel like I'm rushing downward.

863
00:32:12,590 --> 00:32:13,230
Thank you.

864
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:14,110
Here, hold onto me.

865
00:32:14,110 --> 00:32:14,710
Yes, hold her.

866
00:32:14,710 --> 00:32:16,310
I'll hold you.

867
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,680
Yes.

868
00:32:19,830 --> 00:32:20,350
This is fine.

869
00:32:20,350 --> 00:32:21,230
That will do.

870
00:32:21,430 --> 00:32:22,640
We know how to enjoy life.

871
00:32:23,110 --> 00:32:24,190
Slow down.

872
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:32,430
Okay.

873
00:32:32,710 --> 00:32:33,430
Thank you.

874
00:32:33,430 --> 00:32:34,470
You're welcome.

875
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:36,470
We stay here.

876
00:32:36,470 --> 00:32:37,680
Can we take a look?

877
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:38,520
Sure.

878
00:32:39,190 --> 00:32:40,880
Room for three.

879
00:32:42,110 --> 00:32:43,280
The sea view.

880
00:32:45,230 --> 00:32:47,470
These conditions are really good.

881
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,640
Why don't we have a bathtub?

882
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,350
This place is so beautiful.

883
00:32:54,110 --> 00:32:56,000
We are facing the sea.

884
00:32:56,590 --> 00:32:57,520
Swing.

885
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:58,680
I like swings.

886
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,070
Luggage delivered to the door.

887
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:06,470
Thank you.

888
00:33:06,470 --> 00:33:07,070
